  "text": "In the above methods the penalty makes use of the number of parameters in the considered model, put differently the l 0 norm of the vector of parameters. A different line of research addresses the problem by moving to l 1 -the sum of absolute sizes of the coefficients-to penalize the RSS. Methods like the Lasso [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ] and the Dantzig Selector [CITATION_3] ] that take this approach, result in estimators that are not the least squares ones. In most of the proposed methods along the same line, to be reviewed in Section 2.3, there exist a tuning parameter that takes the role that λ does in the sense that it controls the size of the model. The choice of the tuning parameter is based on cross validation ideas, and therefore these methods are computationally more intensive.",
